### Test OTP Authentication Flow with Refresh Tokens

### 1. Send OTP to phone number
POST http://localhost:3001/api/auth/send-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phone": "09123456789"
}

### 2. Verify OTP (replace with actual OTP received)
POST http://localhost:3001/api/auth/verify-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phone": "09123456789",
  "otp": "12345",
  "name": "Test User"
}

### 3. Refresh access token
POST http://localhost:3001/api/auth/refresh-token
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "YOUR_REFRESH_TOKEN_HERE"
}

### 4. Update user profile (requires authentication)
POST http://localhost:3001/api/auth/update-profile
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE

{
  "name": "Updated Name",
  "email": "test@example.com"
}

### 5. Logout (invalidate refresh token)
POST http://localhost:3001/api/auth/logout
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE

{
  "refreshToken": "YOUR_REFRESH_TOKEN_HERE"
}

### 6. Logout from all devices (invalidate all refresh tokens)
POST http://localhost:3001/api/auth/logout
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE

{}
